01:02:38,590 --> 01:02:42,290
- Pretty late.
- Yeah, you too. What did you do?

1085
01:02:42,360 --> 01:02:45,260
I, you know, I worked late...

1086
01:02:45,330 --> 01:02:48,790
and then May and me
had some Chinese food.

1087
01:02:48,870 --> 01:02:51,630
You and May! What'd you talk about
over dinner? Cartoons?

1088
01:02:51,700 --> 01:02:54,330
Are you kiddin'?
We went up to her apartment.

1089
01:02:54,400 --> 01:02:57,070
<i>- We watched White Heat on television.
- Till 3:00 a. m.?</i>

1090
01:02:57,140 --> 01:02:59,510
No. Then we went out
and we got a pizza.

1091
01:02:59,580 --> 01:03:01,740
Chinese food and a pizza?

1092
01:03:01,810 --> 01:03:03,750
With your stomach,
I'm surprised you weren't shot...

1093
01:03:03,810 --> 01:03:05,840
breaking into
the Pepto-Bismol factory.

1094
01:03:05,920 --> 01:03:09,940
<i>No, Frenchy, I had fun. It was the first
time in a long time I had a good time.</i>

1095
01:03:11,720 --> 01:03:14,590
- I want to talk to you, Ray.
- Now?

1096
01:03:14,660 --> 01:03:16,680
David's going over
to Europe for a month.

1097
01:03:16,760 --> 01:03:19,920
I thought we might go along,
see some sights.

1098
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:21,930
What kind of sights?

1099
01:03:22,000 --> 01:03:25,430
<i>You know, churches,
opera houses, ruins.</i>

1100
01:03:25,500 --> 01:03:27,440
What are you, a stroke victim?

1101
01:03:27,500 --> 01:03:30,340
I'm gonna fly 3,000 miles
to see opera houses and ruins?

1102
01:03:30,410 --> 01:03:33,140
- Well, I wanna go.
- What do you mean, you wanna go?

1103
01:03:33,210 --> 01:03:36,410
- It's part of my cultural development.
- Will you knock it off?

1104
01:03:36,480 --> 01:03:39,410
You're Frenchy Fox from New Jersey.
Stop puttin' on airs.

1105
01:03:39,480 --> 01:03:41,750
David thinks that it would be good
for me to travel through Europe.

1106
01:03:41,820 --> 01:03:43,750
<i>I get a bad vibe about this guy.</i>

1107
01:03:43,820 --> 01:03:46,290
Because you're a crook,
so you think everybody is.

1108
01:03:46,360 --> 01:03:49,660
<i>I wish I still was a crook, then
I'd feel like an actual person again.</i>

1109
01:03:49,730 --> 01:03:52,720
I warned you that this would happen
if you didn't grow along with me.

1110
01:03:52,800 --> 01:03:57,030
The only thing that's grown about you is
your rear end from too much French food.

1111
01:03:57,100 --> 01:03:59,470
I'm sorry, Ray,
but I wanna go to Europe.

1112
01:03:59,540 --> 01:04:03,370
What do you mean? We're married.
You can't just go to Europe with David.

1113
01:04:03,440 --> 01:04:05,370
<i>I asked you to come.</i>

1114
01:04:05,440 --> 01:04:08,100
'Cause you knew I'd say no.
That's why you asked me.

1115
01:04:08,180 --> 01:04:12,510
My idea of fun is not goin' to operas
and ruins. I get enough sleep at home.

1116
01:04:12,580 --> 01:04:14,610
<i>I never thought I'd be
saying this to you, Ray,</i>

1117
01:04:14,680 --> 01:04:18,250
but maybe the time has come
to reevaluate our marriage.

1118
01:04:18,320 --> 01:04:20,260
<i>If you go to Europe
with David,</i>

1119
01:04:20,320 --> 01:04:22,290
you're gonna have
to reevaluate it big time.

1120
01:04:22,360 --> 01:04:24,690
I'm going! I won't be
held back mentally...

1121
01:04:24,760 --> 01:04:26,920
by some overaged
juvenile delinquent.

1122
01:04:27,000 --> 01:04:30,830
<i>- Then you better go get yourself a lawyer.
- We don't need lawyers.</i>

1123
01:04:30,900 --> 01:04:34,200
I'll go fifty-fifty with you
even though it's all in my name.

1124
01:04:34,270 --> 01:04:37,000
You're right. We don't need lawyers.
Exactly right, because...

1125
01:04:37,070 --> 01:04:39,130
You don't have to go fifty-fifty.
I don't want anything.

1126
01:04:39,210 --> 01:04:43,150
You can have the house, the business,
custody of all the chocolate chips.

1127
01:04:43,210 --> 01:04:45,440
I just want out.

1128
01:05:20,510 --> 01:05:24,540
[Ray] You know, May, it was on a boat
that I first proposed to Frenchy.

1129
01:05:24,620 --> 01:05:26,550
[May]
Yeah, I know.

1130
01:05:26,620 --> 01:05:30,280
All of a sudden, I'm not her type
after all these years.

1131
01:05:30,350 --> 01:05:34,880
- May I tell you something?
- What?

1132
01:05:34,960 --> 01:05:37,320
You're not my type either.

1133
01:05:37,390 --> 01:05:40,450
What does that mean?
What the hell does that mean?

1134
01:05:40,530 --> 01:05:42,690
It means that maybe Frenchy...

1135
01:05:42,770 --> 01:05:45,290
wasn't so wrong to try
and make something out of herself.

1136
01:05:45,370 --> 01:05:49,100
- Frenchy was nuts! Frenchy overdid everything.
- You underdo everything!

1137
01:05:49,170 --> 01:05:53,440
You know, there's more to life
than turkey meatballs.

1138
01:05:53,510 --> 01:05:57,310
I don't know what to say, May.
I get a bad vibe about this guy, David.

1139
01:05:57,380 --> 01:06:00,610
It's my street instinct,
but I just don't trust him.

1140
01:06:00,680 --> 01:06:02,620
Yeah, I know why.

1141
01:06:02,690 --> 01:06:05,710
Because he's younger than you are,
handsomer than you are,

1142
01:06:05,790 --> 01:06:09,380
he's much taller than you are,
he's smarter than you are,

1143
01:06:09,460 --> 01:06:11,390
he's much more exciting
than you are...

1144
01:06:11,460 --> 01:06:15,800
May, don't feel obligated to pull
any punches with me. I can take it.

1145
01:06:15,870 --> 01:06:21,270
You know, women like a little elegance.
It's more romantic.

1146
01:06:21,340 --> 01:06:24,870
So if I had it to do over again,
I would do some things differently.

1147
01:06:24,940 --> 01:06:28,170
Maybe I'd sit through a couple
of more operas with Frenchy,

1148
01:06:28,250 --> 01:06:31,740
especially now since they got
the new Sony Walkmans.

1149
01:06:31,820 --> 01:06:35,550
Now that you split up with Frenchy,
you don't even work.

1150
01:06:35,620 --> 01:06:40,060
No, I don't work, May,
but I got an idea for something,

1151
01:06:40,120 --> 01:06:42,590
and I wanna talk to you
about it.

1152
01:06:42,660 --> 01:06:44,990
Really?

1153
01:06:55,410 --> 01:06:57,600
<i>[May]
Wow! What a place!</i>

1154
01:06:57,670 --> 01:07:00,010
That's the home of Chi Chi Potter,
the socialite.

1155
01:07:00,080 --> 01:07:02,240
Chi Chi Valezquez Potter.

1156
01:07:02,310 --> 01:07:04,470
Now, Chi Chi's got a necklace.

1157
01:07:04,550 --> 01:07:08,480
It's all emeralds with diamonds
around it. It's a very famous necklace.

1158
01:07:08,550 --> 01:07:11,250
Maybe you saw it in a magazine.
They photograph it all the time.

1159
01:07:11,320 --> 01:07:14,980
- Would it have been on television?
- L-I don't know.

1160
01:07:15,060 --> 01:07:18,520
But it's been in magazines. It's
a famous necklace. I wanna go in there.

1161
01:07:18,600 --> 01:07:22,330
I could live off that necklace
if I fence it for the rest of my life.

1162
01:07:22,400 --> 01:07:25,390
But you gotta remember what happened
when you tunneled into the bank.

1163
01:07:25,470 --> 01:07:28,770
But that's the beauty part.
We don't have to tunnel anymore.

1164
01:07:28,840 --> 01:07:31,870
Now, Frenchy and I,
we're patrons of the arts.

1165
01:07:31,940 --> 01:07:35,070
So Chi Chi invited us to a big party
there in a couple of weeks.

1166
01:07:35,150 --> 01:07:39,010
Frenchy's out of town.
You come with me, we get the necklace.

1167
01:07:39,080 --> 01:07:41,920
Oh, uh, see, I never
heisted anything before.

1168
01:07:41,990 --> 01:07:44,180
There's nothing to it.
I know where the safe is.

1169
01:07:44,250 --> 01:07:46,420
<i>[Ray's Voice] Because this
has been on my mind for a while.</i>

1170
01:07:46,490 --> 01:07:49,150
<i>I had dinner over there one night,
and I excused myself.</i>

1171
01:07:49,230 --> 01:07:52,630
<i>I was very crafty. I went upstairs,
and I checked out the place.</i>

1172
01:07:52,700 --> 01:07:55,290
<i>I scoped it all out,
and I found the safe.</i>

1173
01:07:55,370 --> 01:08:00,860
<i>I got the whole layout in my mind
up there, so I know we can do this.</i>

1174
01:08:23,530 --> 01:08:27,430
I don't wanna wind up in jail. If this
is... Wait. If this is such a big item,

1175
01:08:27,500 --> 01:08:30,800
then they're gonna be turning the town
upside down looking for it.

1176
01:08:30,870 --> 01:08:34,200
No. That's why you're dealing with
a particularly shrewd mentality.

1177
01:08:34,270 --> 01:08:36,260
I got a connection
in Chinatown.

1178
01:08:36,340 --> 01:08:39,900
I bring in a picture that I got
from a magazine of the necklace.

1179
01:08:39,980 --> 01:08:42,840
He makes me an exact duplicate.
I switch.

1180
01:08:42,910 --> 01:08:44,880
She never knows what happened.
She's, you know...

1181
01:08:44,950 --> 01:08:49,080
Chi Chi's a dumb, flighty
society dame. She's crazy.

1182
01:08:49,150 --> 01:08:53,110
By the time she figures out there's a
switch, two years from now or something,

1183
01:08:53,190 --> 01:08:55,660
I'll be in Florida
or The Cayman Islands.

1184
01:08:55,730 --> 01:08:58,160
<i>§[Cello]</i>

1185
01:09:09,140 --> 01:09:11,440
[Cell Phone Ringing]

1186
01:09:13,080 --> 01:09:16,600
[Ringing Continues]

1187
01:09:16,680 --> 01:09:19,670
Hello? What?

1188
01:09:19,750 --> 01:09:22,380
- I can't hear you. What?
- Shh.

1189
01:09:22,450 --> 01:09:24,890
- I'm in a crypt! I can't...
- Please.

1190
01:09:24,960 --> 01:09:28,150
What do you mean?
What are you talking about?

1191
01:09:28,230 --> 01:09:30,590
How? Would you gimme
a break, Sister? Okay?

1192
01:09:30,660 --> 01:09:33,490
What? Today?

1193
01:09:33,560 --> 01:09:37,620
Look, what do you mean
it's an emergency?

1194
01:09:45,940 --> 01:09:48,210
<i>- Oh, hi.
- [Man] Mrs. Winkler?</i>

1195
01:09:48,280 --> 01:09:51,110
<i>We're so sorry to bring you
back from your vacation.</i>

1196
01:09:51,180 --> 01:09:54,810
- What the hell's goin' on, fellas?
- I have terrible news.

1197
01:09:54,890 --> 01:09:58,650
- Something's happened to Ray?
- Sunset Enterprises is bankrupt.

1198
01:09:58,720 --> 01:10:01,450
- How?
- Fraud.

1199
01:10:01,530 --> 01:10:04,690
- Fraud? Who?
- Your accountants.

1200
01:10:04,760 --> 01:10:08,060
My accountants. I don't
even know who they are. What?

1201
01:10:08,130 --> 01:10:10,120
<i>You should've looked.</i>

1202
01:10:10,200 --> 01:10:12,790
We let them handle everything.

1203
01:10:12,870 --> 01:10:15,430
What the hell do I know
about running a corporation?

1204
01:10:15,510 --> 01:10:18,410
<i>Did you ever read anything
you signed?</i>

1205
01:10:18,480 --> 01:10:21,410
No, but they assured us
everything was okay.

1206
01:10:21,480 --> 01:10:23,740
<i>May I get you a drink?</i>

1207
01:10:23,810 --> 01:10:27,010
I'd like a 1961 Romanee St. Vivant
if we have it.

1208
01:10:27,080 --> 01:10:30,310
I'd have a whiskey
if I were you.

1209
01:10:30,390 --> 01:10:32,650
Well, I don't understand.

1210
01:10:32,720 --> 01:10:36,920
I mean, Sunset's gone?
Can't we do anything?

1211
01:10:36,990 --> 01:10:41,290
You might be able to put a few people
in jail if we could find them.

1212
01:10:41,360 --> 01:10:44,270
Oh!
This is the worst news.

1213
01:10:44,330 --> 01:10:46,390
Oh, no, no.
Mrs. Winkler, it's not.

1214
01:10:46,470 --> 01:10:48,400
No?
Well, it is to me!

1215
01:10:48,470 --> 01:10:51,500
No, no, no.
The worst news is coming up.

1216
01:10:52,610 --> 01:10:56,740
Oh. All right.
All right.

1217
01:10:56,810 --> 01:10:59,010
You better tell me.
Let me sit down.

1218
01:10:59,080 --> 01:11:01,680
<i>They spoke to you
about expanding Sunset.</i>

1219
01:11:01,750 --> 01:11:03,810
That's right. We've been
planning it for months. Yeah.

1220
01:11:03,890 --> 01:11:07,450
In order to do that, you needed
a bank loan. Are you aware of that?

1221
01:11:07,520 --> 01:11:11,150
- Quite a substantial loan.
- Get to the point.

1222
01:11:11,230 --> 01:11:14,560
They asked you to sign
a promissory note to the bank.

1223
01:11:14,630 --> 01:11:18,800
You're speaking to the wrong person.
This is what I got accountants for.

1224
01:11:18,870 --> 01:11:22,200
Yes, but unfortunately
your accountants are in Venezuela.

1225
01:11:22,270 --> 01:11:25,330
Wh...
This is all so confusing.

1226
01:11:25,410 --> 01:11:30,350
Frances, you put up your home and
savings as a note for a monster loan.

1227
01:11:32,380 --> 01:11:36,550
Could you put a touch of cyanide
in here? It needs to be stronger.

1228
01:11:36,620 --> 01:11:38,550
You've lost it all, Frenchy.

1229
01:11:38,620 --> 01:11:41,990
Or should I say, you've been
swindled out of it all?

1230
01:11:42,060 --> 01:11:44,030
<i>- You mean, I got...
- Nothing.</i>

1231
01:11:44,090 --> 01:11:48,720
Mrs. Winkler, you have nothing.
No house, no bank account.

1232
01:11:48,800 --> 01:11:51,790
Just a couple of large,
outstanding loans...

1233
01:11:51,870 --> 01:11:55,860
which we feel you can best deal with
by filing for bankruptcy.

1234
01:11:55,940 --> 01:11:57,870
<i>Bankruptcy? Bankruptcy?</i>

1235
01:11:57,940 --> 01:12:01,100
<i>- I'm not up to the "B" words yet.
- Sorry.</i>

1236
01:12:01,180 --> 01:12:03,110
Does Ray know about this?

1237
01:12:03,180 --> 01:12:06,080
<i>What difference does it
make to Ray? He's gone.</i>

1238
01:12:25,830 --> 01:12:28,730
What did you say?

1239
01:12:28,800 --> 01:12:32,820
<i>I'm bankrupt.
Sunset's gone. Worse.</i>

1240
01:12:32,900 --> 01:12:37,170
<i>All my personal dough is gone.
The whole ride's over.</i>

1241
01:12:38,140 --> 01:12:40,570
Well, how...

1242
01:12:40,640 --> 01:12:45,240
- I mean, how could that possibly happen?
- Fraud. My accountants.

1243
01:12:45,310 --> 01:12:49,770
Oh, Ray said not to trust them
because the whole firm had mustaches.

1244
01:12:51,390 --> 01:12:55,290
I'm, I'm gonna get myself
a little Valium.

1245
01:12:55,360 --> 01:12:58,950
<i>David, I'm not gonna be able
to give you that loan I promised you.</i>

1246
01:12:59,030 --> 01:13:00,960
<i>What did you say?</i>

1247
01:13:01,030 --> 01:13:03,290
Suddenly it turns out
I got people I owe.

1248
01:13:03,360 --> 01:13:06,200
I know, but you did say
that I could borrow $400,000.

1249
01:13:06,270 --> 01:13:09,130
- I was using it to cement a deal.
- I know, and it kills me!

1250
01:13:09,200 --> 01:13:13,500
It kills me to cop out on you like this,
but I'm busted. I'm flat.

1251
01:13:13,570 --> 01:13:16,240
- What an idiot.
- I guess I am. Yeah.

1252
01:13:16,310 --> 01:13:20,250
How could you be so stupid
and irresponsible...

1253
01:13:20,310 --> 01:13:24,650
as to allow some patently cheap,
thieving accountants...

1254
01:13:24,720 --> 01:13:26,780
to defraud you
out of a future?

1255
01:13:26,850 --> 01:13:29,320
I just don't understand
how anyone could be that stupid.

1256
01:13:29,390 --> 01:13:31,410
Aren't you
a little out of line?

1257
01:13:31,490 --> 01:13:35,290
<i>Well, you know I've made plans.
I've made commitments to people.</i>

1258
01:13:35,360 --> 01:13:37,630
Wow.

1259
01:13:37,700 --> 01:13:41,630
You've got a strange look in your eye
like the guy from the book.

1260
01:13:41,700 --> 01:13:45,800
Dr. Jekyll or Mr. Hyde or Ted Bundy.
I can never remember.

1261
01:13:45,870 --> 01:13:49,900
Think of the time I've put in nurturing
an idea that's not gonna happen.

1262
01:13:49,980 --> 01:13:52,670
Is that what it was?
The money?

1263
01:13:52,750 --> 01:13:56,200
I, I need... I need my prescription.
I need my little blue pills.

1264
01:13:56,280 --> 01:13:59,180
So I'm gonna go
and get them,

1265
01:13:59,250 --> 01:14:02,810
<i>and I would very, very much appreciate
it if when I came back, you were gone.</i>

1266
01:14:02,890 --> 01:14:05,050
<i>Thank you.</i>

1267
01:14:05,130 --> 01:14:07,920
<i>David, if you wouldn't mind,</i>

1268
01:14:08,000 --> 01:14:12,460
<i>- I'd like the cigarette case back.
- I don't think so, my love.</i>

1269
01:14:13,800 --> 01:14:16,200
Wow.

1270
01:14:16,270 --> 01:14:19,000
I asked you for lessons in life.

1271
01:14:19,070 --> 01:14:21,870
I guess I really got one, right?

1272
01:14:39,230 --> 01:14:42,160
Oh, we're so glad you could come!

1273
01:14:42,230 --> 01:14:44,700
- How are you?
- Good.

1274
01:14:44,770 --> 01:14:50,100
Langston wants to talk to you
about a theater project in Aspen.

1275
01:14:50,170 --> 01:14:53,260
- Do you ski?
- Me? No, never. Never.

1276
01:14:53,340 --> 01:14:57,940
- Do either of you play miniature golf?
- Oh, there's Binky!

1277
01:14:58,010 --> 01:15:01,310
- Oh, hello!
- Oh, for heaven's sake.

1278
01:15:01,380 --> 01:15:04,150
Mingle.

1279
01:15:04,220 --> 01:15:07,480
I don't think you should speak.
I don't think you should say anything.

1280
01:15:07,550 --> 01:15:10,110
But you said make conversation.
I was just making it.

1281
01:15:10,190 --> 01:15:14,850
I know. Make conversation,
but don't talk. Don't bring up anything.

1282
01:15:14,930 --> 01:15:18,160
Maybe about the weather or something,
but don't... You know.

1283
01:15:18,230 --> 01:15:22,630
Now, I'm gonna get in the flow of things
here and then I'm gonna glide upstairs.

1284
01:15:22,700 --> 01:15:25,830
- Should I glide with you?
- No, no. I'll contact you.

1285
01:15:25,910 --> 01:15:29,770
- Can I get you some champagne?
- Sure.

1286
01:15:46,160 --> 01:15:48,320
<i>[Woman]
Ray?</i>

1287
01:15:49,930 --> 01:15:52,190
I was ju...
I was gonna make a phone call.

1288
01:15:52,270 --> 01:15:55,030
- Have you seen Edgar?
- Edgar?

1289
01:15:55,100 --> 01:15:58,660
- Where that man gets off to!
- I was gonna make a phone...

1290
01:15:58,740 --> 01:16:01,640
I've looked back here,
and downstairs.

1291
01:16:01,710 --> 01:16:04,370
- Try back there.
- I'll try that. Thank you.

1292
01:16:20,130 --> 01:16:22,060
<i>[Adams]
Oh, Winkler?</i>

1293
01:16:22,130 --> 01:16:24,890
<i>- Do you play golf?
- Golf? No.</i>

1294
01:16:24,970 --> 01:16:27,160
I was just gonna make
a phone call upstairs.

1295
01:16:27,230 --> 01:16:32,470
- I guess I was misdirected.
- Yes, well, I was gonna use the phone.

1296
01:16:32,540 --> 01:16:36,340
I'm sorry. I wanted a match on Sunday,
but I'll get somebody else.

1297
01:16:36,410 --> 01:16:38,640
I would've looked
forward to it.

1298
